{"version":"0.9.5","fields":["title","body","keywords"],"ref":"id","documentStore":{"docs":{"index.html":{"id":"index.html","title":"About","keywords":"AsciiDoc,documentation pipeline,Maven,PDF,IKE Community,knowledge engineering","body":"About IKE Minimal Fonts Minimal Noto font subset for IKE documentation (~4MB)"},"summary.html":{"id":"summary.html","title":"Project Summary","keywords":"AsciiDoc,documentation pipeline,Maven,PDF,IKE Community,knowledge engineering","body":"Project Summary Project Information Field Value Name IKE Minimal Fonts Description Minimal Noto font subset for IKE documentation (~4MB) Homepage https://github.com/IKE-Network/ike-minimal-fonts[1] Project Organization Field Value Name IKE Community URL https://ike.network[2] Build Information Field Value GroupId network.ike ArtifactId minimal-fonts Version 55 Type jar Java Version 25"},"licenses.html":{"id":"licenses.html","title":"Project Licenses","keywords":"AsciiDoc,documentation pipeline,Maven,PDF,IKE Community,knowledge engineering","body":"Overview Typically the licenses listed for the project are that of the project itself, and not of dependencies. Project Licenses SIL Open Font License 1.1 All fonts from Google Noto project, licensed under SIL OFL 1.1. Text fonts: notofonts/latin-greek-cyrillic (NotoSans v2.015, NotoSerif v2.015, NotoSansMono v2.014) Math font: notofonts/math (NotoSansMath v3.000) Symbol fonts: notofonts/symbols (NotoSansSymbols v2.003, NotoSansSymbols2 v2.008) [Original text][1] Copy of the license follows: [2] SIL Open Font License [3]OFL Text [4]How [5]Why [6]Fonts [7]History The SIL Open Font License The widely used, community-approved, free, libre, and open source license specifically designed for fonts and related software: a solid legal framework for worldwide development, sharing, and improvement of fonts and related software in a collaborative manner. Welcome to the new OFL website! You may have been redirected here from the old site on scripts.sil.org/OFL. The domain and website have changed to make everything clearer but the OFL itself has remained unchanged since 2007. We welcome your feedback.[8] On November 22, 2025 we celebrated the 20th birthday of the OFL version 1.0 release! 🎂🎉🥳 Happy birthday and a big thank you to everyone who contributed to and benefited from the OFL over the last two decades: users, designers, publishers, advocates, donors, sponsors and funders! Current version: SIL Open Font License (OFL) version 1.1 Read or download the full official license text: OFL version 1.1 (26 February 2007)[9] Read or download the current OFL-FAQ version 1.1-update7 (November 2023)[10] Read more about why many individuals and companies choose the OFL[11] and the history of the OFL[12] Explore a showcase of fonts released under the OFL[13] Answers to common questions If you use OFL fonts You can use them in books, posters, artwork, logos, and on websites, even make 3D objects with the outlines—no acknowledgement is required You can bundle them in apps or software subject to certain conditions Read more about using OFL fonts[14] If you modify OFL fonts You can freely modify and redistribute OFL fonts Some projects may require a name change to respect any declared Reserved Font Names (RFNs) Read more about modifying OFL fonts and managing RFNs[15] If you design OFL fonts You retain copyright on your creation and are acknowledged as the author You can protect the name of your font with one or more Reserved Font Names (RFNs) Read more about applying the OFL to your fonts[16] About SIL SIL[17] is a global, faith-based nonprofit that works with local communities around the world to develop language solutions that expand possibilities for a better life. We help build capacity for sustainable language development by means of research, translation, training, and materials development. We want to enable others to participate in our projects, share our knowledge and experience around writing systems, and equip the wider community to meet local and global font needs. We are grateful to those that fund our work. Please visit Donate to SIL’s WSTech[18] for information on supporting our efforts. [17] The SIL Open Font License is maintained by Victor Gaultney and Nicolas Spalinger. Contact us[8]. This site is Copyright © 2005–2026 SIL International (sil.org)[17] | Privacy policy[19] | Colophon[20] | Site map[21]"},"dependency-info.html":{"id":"dependency-info.html","title":"Maven Coordinates","keywords":"AsciiDoc,documentation pipeline,Maven,PDF,IKE Community,knowledge engineering","body":"Maven Coordinates Apache Maven <dependency>\n  <groupId>network.ike</groupId>\n  <artifactId>minimal-fonts</artifactId>\n  <version>55</version>\n</dependency> Apache Ivy <dependency org=\"network.ike\" name=\"minimal-fonts\" rev=\"55\">\n  <artifact name=\"minimal-fonts\" type=\"jar\" />\n</dependency> Groovy Grape @Grapes(\n@Grab(group='network.ike', module='minimal-fonts', version='55')\n) Gradle/Grails implementation 'network.ike:minimal-fonts:55' Scala SBT libraryDependencies += \"network.ike\" % \"minimal-fonts\" % \"55\" Leiningen [network.ike/minimal-fonts \"55\"]"},"project-info.html":{"id":"project-info.html","title":"Project Information","keywords":"AsciiDoc,documentation pipeline,Maven,PDF,IKE Community,knowledge engineering","body":"Project Information This document provides an overview of the various documents and links that are part of this project's general information. All of this content is automatically generated by Maven[1] on behalf of the project. Overview Document Description About[2] Minimal Noto font subset for IKE documentation (~4MB) Summary[3] This document lists other related information of this project Licenses[4] This document lists the project license(s). Maven Coordinates[5] This document describes how to include this project as a dependency using various dependency management tools."}},"docInfo":{"index.html":{"title":0,"body":10,"keywords":4},"summary.html":{"title":2,"bod